{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775901540559,"sessionID":"ses_28405544effe3GThej4vtHVoCj","part":{"id":"prt_d7bfaf2da0014bB1xDNCHcK4mc","messageID":"msg_d7bfad680001d5XtsBK1LBuESF","sessionID":"ses_28405544effe3GThej4vtHVoCj","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:5","state":{"status":"error","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-026/plan.md"},"error":"File not found: /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-026/plan.md","time":{"start":1775901540547,"end":1775901540558}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775901540560,"sessionID":"ses_28405544effe3GThej4vtHVoCj","part":{"id":"prt_d7bfaf755001rUSApnjEqM5FvX","messageID":"msg_d7bfad680001d5XtsBK1LBuESF","sessionID":"ses_28405544effe3GThej4vtHVoCj","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:6","state":{"status":"error","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-026/design.md"},"error":"File not found: /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-026/design.md","time":{"start":1775901540549,"end":1775901540559}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775901540575,"sessionID":"ses_28405544effe3GThej4vtHVoCj","part":{"id":"prt_d7bfaee46001hI5Rtx5c7N0Npt","messageID":"msg_d7bfad680001d5XtsBK1LBuESF","sessionID":"ses_28405544effe3GThej4vtHVoCj","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-026/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-026/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification: K8s/AgentCube Provider (AR-026)\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-026  \n6: **Module:** cmd/cli  \n7: **Language:** Python  \n8: **Size:** M  \n9: **Target:** `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`, `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n10: \n11: This delta specification defines the behavior and acceptance criteria for the Kubernetes provider classes that handle agent deployment to both standard Kubernetes (Deployment/Service) and AgentCube custom resources (AgentRuntime CR).\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — Initialization and Configuration\n18: \n19: The system SHALL provide `KubernetesProvider` to interact with Kubernetes clusters for deploying agents using standard Kubernetes resources (Deployment + NodePort Service).\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Initialize with default namespace\n22: - **GIVEN** no namespace is provided\n23: - **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider()` is instantiated\n24: - **THEN** it SHALL default `namespace` to `\"default\"`, `verbose` to `False`, and `kubeconfig` to `None`\n25: \n26: #### Scenario: Initialize with custom namespace\n27: - **GIVEN** `namespace=\"my-namespace\"`, `verbose=True`, and `kubeconfig=\"/path/to/kubeconfig\"`\n28: - **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider(...)` is instantiated\n29: - **THEN** it SHALL store these values and configure the Kubernetes client accordingly\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Initialize with kubeconfig from environment\n32: - **GIVEN** `kubeconfig` is `None` and environment variable `KUBECONFIG` is set\n33: - **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider()` is instantiated\n34: - **THEN** it SHALL use the kubernetes client with default configuration (likely from `~/.kube/config` or in-cluster config)\n35: \n36: #### Scenario: Verbose logging during initialization\n37: - **GIVEN** `verbose=True`\n38: - **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider(verbose=True)` is instantiated\n39: - **THEN** it SHALL log initialization details including namespace configuration\n40: \n41: ---\n42: \n43: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — Namespace Management\n44: \n45: The system SHALL ensure the target namespace exists before deploying resources.\n46: \n47: #### Scenario: Namespace already exists\n48: - **GIVEN** the namespace `\"my-namespace\"` already exists in the cluster\n49: - **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace()` is called\n50: - **THEN** it SHALL not raise an error and continue without creating the namespace again\n51: \n52: #### Scenario: Namespace does not exist\n53: - **GIVEN** the namespace `\"new-namespace\"` does not exist in the cluster\n54: - **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace()` is called\n55: - **THEN** it SHALL create the namespace using the Kubernetes API\n56: \n57: #### Scenario: Namespace creation failure\n58: - **GIVEN** the user lacks permission to create namespaces\n59: - **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace()` attempts to create a namespace\n60: - **THEN** it SHALL raise an appropriate exception (e.g., `ApiException` or permission error)\n61: \n62: ---\n63: \n64: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — Name Sanitization\n65: \n66: The system SHALL sanitize agent names to comply with Kubernetes resource naming conventions.\n67: \n68: #### Scenario: Valid name passed through\n69: - **GIVEN** an agent name `\"my-agent\"`\n70: - **WHEN** `_sanitize_name(\"my-agent\")` is called\n71: - **THEN** it SHALL return `\"my-agent\"` unchanged\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: Uppercase letters converted to lowercase\n74: - **GIVEN** an agent name `\"My-Agent\"`\n75: - **WHEN** `_sanitize_name(\"My-Agent\")` is called\n76: - **THEN** it SHALL return `\"my-agent\"` (lowercase)\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: Invalid characters replaced\n79: - **GIVEN** an agent name `\"my_agent@v1.0\"`\n80: - **WHEN** `_sanitize_name(\"my_agent@v1.0\")` is called\n81: - **THEN** it SHALL return a sanitized version with invalid characters replaced or removed\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Long names truncated\n84: - **GIVEN** an agent name exceeding 63 characters (Kubernetes DNS label limit)\n85: - **WHEN** `_sanitize_name()` is called\n86: - **THEN** it SHALL truncate the name to comply with Kubernetes naming constraints\n87: \n88: ---\n89: \n90: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — Agent Deployment\n91: \n92: The system SHALL deploy agents as Kubernetes Deployment and NodePort Service resources.\n93: \n94: #### Scenario: Deploy agent with minimal configuration\n95: - **GIVEN** `agent_name=\"hello-agent\"`, `image_url=\"hello:v1.0.0\"`, `port=8080`\n96: - **WHEN** `deploy_agent(agent_name, image_url, port)` is called\n97: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n98:   1. Ensure namespace exists\n99:   2. Create a Deployment with the specified image and port\n100:   3. Create a NodePort Service exposing the port\n101:   4. Return deployment info including `deployment_name`, `service_name`, `namespace`, `replicas`, `container_port`, `node_port`, and `service_url`\n102: \n103: #### Scenario: Deploy agent with custom entrypoint\n104: - **GIVEN** `entrypoint=\"python /app/main.py\"` and other required parameters\n105: - **WHEN** `deploy_agent(...)` is called\n106: - **THEN** the Deployment SHALL include the entrypoint as the container command\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: Deploy agent with multiple replicas\n109: - **GIVEN** `replicas=3` and other required parameters\n110: - **WHEN** `deploy_agent(...)` is called\n111: - **THEN** the Deployment SHALL specify `replicas: 3`\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: Deploy agent with specific NodePort\n114: - **GIVEN** `node_port=30080` (within valid range 30000-32767)\n115: - **WHEN** `deploy_agent(...)` is called\n116: - **THEN** the Service SHALL use the specified NodePort, and `service_url` SHALL be `\"http://localhost:30080\"`\n117: \n118: #### Scenario: Deploy agent with auto-assigned NodePort\n119: - **GIVEN** `node_port=None`\n120: - **WHEN** `deploy_agent(...)` is called\n121: - **THEN** Kubernetes SHALL auto-assign a NodePort in range 30000-32767, and the returned `service_url` SHALL reflect the assigned port\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: Deploy agent with environment variables\n124: - **GIVEN** `env_vars={\"LOG_LEVEL\": \"debug\", \"ENV\": \"production\"}`\n125: - **WHEN** `deploy_agent(...)` is called\n126: - **THEN** the Deployment container SHALL include the specified environment variables\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Deploy when Deployment already exists\n129: - **GIVEN** a Deployment with the same name already exists\n130: - **WHEN** `deploy_agent(...)` is called\n131: - **THEN** it SHALL update/patch the existing Deployment with new configuration (e.g., new image)\n132: \n133: ---\n134: \n135: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — Deployment Resource Creation\n136: \n137: The system SHALL create properly configured Kubernetes Deployment resources.\n138: \n139: #### Scenario: Create deployment with defaults\n140: - **GIVEN** minimal required parameters\n141: - **WHEN** `_create_deployment(name, image_url, port, None, 1, None)` is called\n142: - **THEN** it SHALL return a Deployment configuration dict with:\n143:   - `apiVersion: apps/v1`\n144:   - `kind: Deployment`\n145:   - Proper selector labels matching the agent name\n146:   - Container specification with the image and port\n147: \n148: #### Scenario: Create deployment with entrypoint\n149: - **GIVEN** `entrypoint=\"python main.py\"`\n150: - **WHEN** `_create_deployment(...)` is called\n151: - **THEN** the container spec SHALL include `\"command\": [\"python\", \"main.py\"]`\n152: \n153: #### Scenario: Create deployment with replicas\n154: - **GIVEN** `replicas=5`\n155: - **WHEN** `_create_deployment(...)` is called\n156: - **THEN** the spec SHALL include `\"replicas\": 5`\n157: \n158: #### Scenario: Create deployment with env vars\n159: - **GIVEN** `env_vars={\"KEY\": \"value\"}`\n160: - **WHEN** `_create_deployment(...)` is called\n161: - **THEN** the container spec SHALL include `\"env\": [{\"name\": \"KEY\", \"value\": \"value\"}]`\n162: \n163: ---\n164: \n165: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — Service Resource Creation\n166: \n167: The system SHALL create properly configured Kubernetes NodePort Service resources.\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: Create service with specific NodePort\n170: - **GIVEN** `port=8080`, `node_port=30080`\n171: - **WHEN** `_create_service(name=\"my-agent\", port=8080, node_port=30080)` is called\n172: - **THEN** it SHALL return a Service configuration with:\n173:   - `type: NodePort`\n174:   - `ports` containing `port`, `targetPort`, and `nodePort`\n175:   - Selector matching the Deployment labels\n176: \n177: #### Scenario: Create service with auto-assigned NodePort\n178: - **GIVEN** `node_port=None`\n179: - **WHEN** `_create_service(...)` is called\n180: - **THEN** the service spec SHALL omit `nodePort`, allowing Kubernetes to auto-assign\n181: \n182: #### Scenario: Service selector matches deployment\n183: - **GIVEN** an agent name `\"my-agent\"`\n184: - **WHEN** `_create_service(\"my-agent\", ...)` is called\n185: - **THEN** the service selector SHALL match the labels on the deployment pods\n186: \n187: ---\n188: \n189: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — Deployment Readiness Waiting\n190: \n191: The system SHALL wait for deployments to become ready before considering them available.\n192: \n193: #### Scenario: Wait for deployment succeeds\n194: - **GIVEN** a deployment that becomes ready within timeout\n195: - **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready(name=\"my-agent\", timeout=120)` is called\n196: - **THEN** it SHALL return without error once all replicas are ready\n197: \n198: #### Scenario: Wait for deployment times out\n199: - **GIVEN** a deployment that fails to become ready (e.g., image pull failure)\n200: - **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready(name=\"my-agent\", timeout=120)` is called\n201: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `TimeoutError` after 120 seconds\n202: \n203: #### Scenario: Custom timeout value\n204: - **GIVEN** `timeout=60`\n205: - **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready(...)` is called\n206: - **THEN** it SHALL wait up to 60 seconds before raising `TimeoutError`\n207: \n208: #### Scenario: Verbose logging during wait\n209: - **GIVEN** `verbose=True`\n210: - **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready()` executes\n211: - **THEN** it SHALL log status updates including replica counts and readiness status\n212: \n213: ---\n214: \n215: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — Agent Status Retrieval\n216: \n217: The system SHALL retrieve the current status of deployed agents.\n218: \n219: #### Scenario: Get status for running agent\n220: - **GIVEN** a running Deployment with available replicas\n221: - **WHEN** `get_agent_status(agent_name=\"my-agent\")` is called\n222: - **THEN** it SHALL return status dict including `status` (e.g., \"running\"), `replicas`, `available_replicas`, and `service_url`\n223: \n224: #### Scenario: Get status for non-existent agent\n225: - **GIVEN** no Deployment exists for the agent name\n226: - **WHEN** `get_agent_status(agent_name=\"missing-agent\")` is called\n227: - **THEN** it SHALL return a status indicating the agent is not found (e.g., `status=\"not_found\"`)\n228: \n229: #### Scenario: Get status for scaling deployment\n230: - **GIVEN** a Deployment currently scaling (e.g., rolling update in progress)\n231: - **WHEN** `get_agent_status(...)` is called\n232: - **THEN** it SHALL return status indicating the current state (e.g., `status=\"scaling\"` or show replica mismatch)\n233: \n234: ---\n235: \n236: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — Agent Deletion\n237: \n238: The system SHALL properly delete deployed agents and their associated resources.\n239: \n240: #### Scenario: Delete existing agent\n241: - **GIVEN** an agent with existing Deployment and Service\n242: - **WHEN** `delete_agent(agent_name=\"my-agent\")` is called\n243: - **THEN** it SHALL delete both the Deployment and Service, and return `{\"status\": \"deleted\", \"deployment_name\": \"my-agent\", \"namespace\": \"default\"}`\n244: \n245: #### Scenario: Delete non-existent agent (idempotent)\n246: - **GIVEN** no resources exist for the agent name\n247: - **WHEN** `delete_agent(agent_name=\"missing-agent\")` is called\n248: - **THEN** it SHALL ignore the 404 errors and return deletion confirmation\n249: \n250: #### Scenario: Delete agent with specific namespace\n251: - **GIVEN** an agent deployed in namespace `\"production\"`\n252: - **WHEN** `delete_agent(agent_name=\"my-agent\")` is called on a provider initialized with `namespace=\"production\"`\n253: - **THEN** it SHALL delete resources from the correct namespace\n254: \n255: ---\n256: \n257: ### Requirement: AgentCubeProvider — Initialization\n258: \n259: The system SHALL provide `AgentCubeProvider` to deploy agents using the AgentRuntime Custom Resource.\n260: \n261: #### Scenario: Initialize with defaults\n262: - **GIVEN** no parameters provided\n263: - **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider()` is instantiated\n264: - **THEN** it SHALL default `namespace` to `\"default\"` and `verbose` to `False`\n265: \n266: #### Scenario: Initialize with custom parameters\n267: - **GIVEN** `namespace=\"agentcube-system\"`, `verbose=True`, `kubeconfig=None`\n268: - **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider(...)` is instantiated\n269: - **THEN** it SHALL store these configuration values\n270: \n271: ---\n272: \n273: ### Requirement: AgentCubeProvider — AgentRuntime CR Deployment\n274: \n275: The system SHALL deploy agents as AgentRuntime Custom Resources for the AgentCube platform.\n276: \n277: #### Scenario: Deploy AgentRuntime with minimal configuration\n278: - **GIVEN** `agent_name=\"my-runtime\"`, `image_url=\"myimage:v1.0\"`, `port=8080`\n279: - **WHEN** `deploy_agent_runtime(agent_name, image_url, port)` is called\n280: - **THEN** it SHALL create an AgentRuntime CR in the configured namespace and return deployment info\n281: \n282: #### Scenario: Deploy AgentRuntime with readiness probe\n283: - **GIVEN** `readiness_probe_path=\"/health\"` and `readiness_probe_port=8080`\n284: - **WHEN** `deploy_agent_runtime(...)` is called\n285: - **THEN** the CR spec SHALL include readiness probe configuration\n286: \n287: #### Scenario: Deploy AgentRuntime with environment variables from URLs\n288: - **GIVEN** `workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\"`, `router_url=\"http://router:8080\"`, and `env_vars=None`\n289: - **WHEN** `deploy_agent_runtime(...)` is called\n290: - **THEN** it SHALL set `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` and `ROUTER_URL` environment variables automatically\n291: \n292: #### Scenario: Deploy AgentRuntime with custom env vars and URLs\n293: - **GIVEN** `env_vars={\"CUSTOM\": \"value\"}`, `workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\"`\n294: - **WHEN** `deploy_agent_runtime(...)` is called\n295: - **THEN** the resulting env SHALL contain both custom vars and the auto-injected WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n296: \n297: #### Scenario: Deploy AgentRuntime with default timeout settings\n298: - **GIVEN** no session timeout parameters provided\n299: - **WHEN** `deploy_agent_runtime(...)` is called\n300: - **THEN** the CR spec SHALL include `sessionTimeout: \"15m\"` and `maxSessionDuration: \"8h\"`\n301: \n302: #### Scenario: Deploy AgentRuntime with image pull secrets\n303: - **GIVEN** any valid deployment parameters\n304: - **WHEN** `deploy_agent_runtime(...)` is called\n305: - **THEN** the CR spec SHALL include `imagePullSecrets: [{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]`\n306: \n307: #### Scenario: Deploy AgentRuntime with entrypoint\n308: - **GIVEN** `entrypoint=\"python /app/server.py\"`\n309: - **WHEN** `deploy_agent_runtime(...)` is called\n310: - **THEN** the CR spec SHALL include the entrypoint in the container configuration\n311: \n312: #### Scenario: Update existing AgentRuntime\n313: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime CR with the same name already exists\n314: - **WHEN** `deploy_agent_runtime(...)` is called with a different image\n315: - **THEN** it SHALL patch/update the existing CR with the new configuration\n316: \n317: ---\n318: \n319: ### Requirement: AgentCubeProvider — AgentRuntime CR Retrieval\n320: \n321: The system SHALL retrieve AgentRuntime Custom Resources by name and namespace.\n322: \n323: #### Scenario: Get existing AgentRuntime\n324: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime CR named `\"my-runtime\"` exists in namespace `\"default\"`\n325: - **WHEN** `get_agent_runtime(name=\"my-runtime\", namespace=\"default\")` is called\n326: - **THEN** it SHALL return the CR object as a dict\n327: \n328: #### Scenario: Get non-existent AgentRuntime\n329: - **GIVEN** no AgentRuntime CR exists with the specified name\n330: - **WHEN** `get_agent_runtime(name=\"missing-runtime\", namespace=\"default\")` is called\n331: - **THEN** it SHALL return `None`\n332: \n333: #### Scenario: Get AgentRuntime with custom API group\n334: - **GIVEN** the CRD is defined for `group=\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"`, `version=\"v1alpha1\"`, `plural=\"agentruntimes\"`\n335: - **WHEN** `get_agent_runtime(...)` is called\n336: - **THEN** it SHALL use the correct API group/version when calling the Kubernetes API\n337: \n338: ---\n339: \n340: ### Requirement: AgentCubeProvider — Namespace Management\n341: \n342: The system SHALL ensure namespace exists before deploying AgentRuntime CRs.\n343: \n344: #### Scenario: Ensure namespace for AgentRuntime\n345: - **GIVEN** the target namespace does not exist\n346: - **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace()` is called\n347: - **THEN** it SHALL create the namespace using Kubernetes API\n348: \n349: #### Scenario: Namespace already exists for AgentRuntime\n350: - **GIVEN** the target namespace exists\n351: - **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace()` is called\n352: - **THEN** it SHALL proceed without error\n353: \n354: ---\n355: \n356: ### Requirement: AgentCubeProvider — Name Sanitization\n357: \n358: The system SHALL sanitize names for AgentRuntime CRs using the same logic as KubernetesProvider.\n359: \n360: #### Scenario: Sanitize AgentRuntime name\n361: - **GIVEN** an agent name `\"My_Runtime@Prod\"`\n362: - **WHEN** `_sanitize_name(\"My_Runtime@Prod\")` is called\n363: - **THEN** it SHALL return a Kubernetes-compliant name (lowercase, valid characters only)\n364: \n365: ---\n366: \n367: ### Requirement: Provider Integration — PublishRuntime Provider Selection\n368: \n369: The system SHALL use the appropriate provider based on the `provider` parameter.\n370: \n371: #### Scenario: Publish with K8s provider\n372: - **GIVEN** `provider=\"k8s\"` in CLI or runtime options\n373: - **WHEN** `PublishRuntime.publish(...)` is called\n374: - **THEN** it SHALL use `KubernetesProvider` to deploy the agent\n375: \n376: #### Scenario: Publish with AgentCube provider\n377: - **GIVEN** `provider=\"agentcube\"` in CLI or runtime options\n378: - **WHEN** `PublishRuntime.publish(...)` is called\n379: - **THEN** it SHALL use `AgentCubeProvider` to deploy the AgentRuntime CR\n380: \n381: #### Scenario: Invalid provider raises error\n382: - **GIVEN** `provider=\"invalid-provider\"`\n383: - **WHEN** `PublishRuntime` attempts to deploy\n384: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` with message indicating invalid provider\n385: \n386: ---\n387: \n388: ### Requirement: Provider Integration — PublishRuntime Prerequisites\n389: \n390: The system SHALL validate prerequisites before deploying with AgentCube provider.\n391: \n392: #### Scenario: AgentCube provider requires router_url and workload_manager_url\n393: - **GIVEN** `provider=\"agentcube\"` and metadata lacks `router_url` or `workload_manager_url`\n394: - **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._publish_cr_to_k8s()` is called\n395: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` with message requiring both fields in `agent_metadata.yaml`\n396: \n397: #### Scenario: K8s provider does not require AgentCube URLs\n398: - **GIVEN** `provider=\"k8s\"` and metadata has no `router_url` or `workload_manager_url`\n399: - **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._publish_k8s()` is called\n400: - **THEN** it SHALL proceed with deployment without requiring these fields\n401: \n402: ---\n403: \n404: ### Requirement: Provider Integration — StatusRuntime Provider Selection\n405: \n406: The system SHALL support status retrieval for both provider types.\n407: \n408: #### Scenario: Status for K8s deployment\n409: - **GIVEN** `provider=\"k8s\"` and agent was deployed with KubernetesProvider\n410: - **WHEN** `StatusRuntime.get_status(...)` is called\n411: - **THEN** it SHALL call `_get_k8s_status()` and return Deployment status\n412: \n413: #### Scenario: Status for AgentCube CR\n414: - **GIVEN** `provider=\"agentcube\"` and agent was deployed as AgentRuntime CR\n415: - **WHEN** `StatusRuntime.get_status(...)` is called\n416: - **THEN** it SHALL call `_get_cr_k8s_status()` and return CR status\n417: \n418: ---\n419: \n420: ### Requirement: StatusRuntime — CR Status Interpretation\n421: \n422: The system SHALL correctly interpret AgentRuntime CR status fields.\n423: \n424: #### Scenario: CR has status fields\n425: - **GIVEN** the CR object has `\"status\"` key with `\"status\"` and `\"agentEndpoint\"` subfields\n426: - **WHEN** `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status()` processes it\n427: - **THEN** it SHALL extract and return these status values\n428: \n429: #### Scenario: CR exists but has no status\n430: - **GIVEN** the CR object exists but lacks a `\"status\"` key\n431: - **WHEN** `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status()` processes it\n432: - **THEN** it SHALL return `status=\"created_no_status\"`\n433: \n434: #### Scenario: CR not found in K8s\n435: - **GIVEN** the CR does not exist in the cluster\n436: - **WHEN** `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status()` is called\n437: - **THEN** it SHALL return `status=\"not_found_in_k8s\"`\n438: \n439: ---\n440: \n441: ### Requirement: Provider Integration — InvokeRuntime Provider Selection\n442: \n443: The system SHALL route invocations through the correct provider.\n444: \n445: #### Scenario: Invoke AgentCube provider endpoint\n446: - **GIVEN** `provider=\"agentcube\"` and `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`\n447: - **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke(...)` is called\n448: - **THEN** it SHALL construct endpoint as `{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n449: \n450: #### Scenario: Invoke K8s provider directly\n451: - **GIVEN** `provider=\"k8s\"` or direct endpoint is configured\n452: - **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke(...)` is called\n453: - **THEN** it SHALL POST to the configured `agent_endpoint` or service URL directly\n454: \n455: ---\n456: \n457: ### Requirement: Error Handling — Kubernetes API Errors\n458: \n459: The system SHALL handle Kubernetes API errors gracefully.\n460: \n461: #### Scenario: Kubernetes connection failure\n462: - **GIVEN** the cluster is unreachable\n463: - **WHEN** any provider method attempts to call Kubernetes API\n464: - **THEN** it SHALL raise an appropriate exception (e.g., connection error) with descriptive message\n465: \n466: #### Scenario: Permission denied\n467: - **GIVEN** the user lacks RBAC permissions for the operation\n468: - **WHEN** any provider method is called\n469: - **THEN** it SHALL propagate the `ApiException` with status 403\n470: \n471: #### Scenario: Resource already exists\n472: - **GIVEN** attempting to create a resource that already exists (and patch is not working)\n473: - **WHEN** `deploy_agent()` or `deploy_agent_runtime()` is called\n474: - **THEN** it SHALL handle the conflict appropriately (update existing or raise error)\n475: \n476: ---\n477: \n478: ### Requirement: Error Handling — Validation Errors\n479: \n480: The system SHALL validate inputs before calling Kubernetes API.\n481: \n482: #### Scenario: Invalid NodePort range\n483: - **GIVEN** `node_port=29999` (below 30000)\n484: - **WHEN** `deploy_agent(...)` is called\n485: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating NodePort must be in range 30000-32767\n486: \n487: #### Scenario: Invalid port number\n488: - **GIVEN** `port=70000` (exceeds 65535)\n489: - **WHEN** `deploy_agent(...)` is called\n490: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating invalid port number\n491: \n492: #### Scenario: Empty agent name\n493: - **GIVEN** `agent_name=\"\"` or `agent_name=None`\n494: - **WHEN** provider deployment methods are called\n495: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` requiring a valid agent name\n496: \n497: #### Scenario: Empty image URL\n498: - **GIVEN** `image_url=\"\"` or `image_url=None`\n499: - **WHEN** provider deployment methods are called\n500: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` requiring a valid image URL\n501: \n502: ---\n503: \n504: ## Data Model Reference\n505: \n506: ### KubernetesProvider Class\n507: \n508: ```python\n509: class KubernetesProvider:\n510:     def __init__(\n511:         self,\n512:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n513:         verbose: bool = False,\n514:         kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n515:     ) -> None: ...\n516:     def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None: ...\n517:     def deploy_agent(\n518:         self,\n519:         agent_name: str,\n520:         image_url: str,\n521:         port: int,\n522:         entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n523:         replicas: int = 1,\n524:         node_port: Optional[int] = None,\n525:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n526:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n527:     def _create_deployment(\n528:         self,\n529:         name: str,\n530:         image_url: str,\n531:         port: int,\n532:         entrypoint: Optional[str],\n533:         replicas: int,\n534:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n535:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n536:     def _create_service(\n537:         self,\n538:         name: str,\n539:         port: int,\n540:         node_port: Optional[int]\n541:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n542:     def wait_for_deployment_ready(self, name: str, timeout: int = 120) -> None: ...\n543:     def get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n544:     def delete_agent(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n545:     def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str: ...\n546: ```\n547: \n548: ### AgentCubeProvider Class\n549: \n550: ```python\n551: class AgentCubeProvider:\n552:     def __init__(\n553:         self,\n554:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n555:         verbose: bool = False,\n556:         kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n557:     ) -> None: ...\n558:     def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None: ...\n559:     def deploy_agent_runtime(\n560:         self,\n561:         agent_name: str,\n562:         image_url: str,\n563:         port: int,\n564:         entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n565:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n566:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n567:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n568:         readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None,\n569:         readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None,\n570:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n571:     def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str: ...\n572:     def get_agent_runtime(self, name: str, namespace: str) -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]]: ...\n573: ```\n574: \n575: ---\n576: \n577: ## File Index\n578: \n579: | Path | Purpose |\n580: |------|---------|\n581: | `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | `KubernetesProvider` class implementation |\n582: | `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | `AgentCubeProvider` class implementation |\n583: | `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Services package exports |\n584: \n585: ---\n586: \n587: ## Dependencies\n588: \n589: | Dependency | Purpose |\n590: |------------|---------|\n591: | `kubernetes>=28.0.0` | Kubernetes Python client for API interactions |\n592: | `pydantic>=2.0.0` | Data validation (via `AgentMetadata`) |\n593: | `PyYAML>=6.0` | YAML parsing for kubeconfig |\n594: \n595: ---\n596: \n597: ## Integration Points\n598: \n599: | Component | Integration |\n600: |-----------|-------------|\n601: | `PublishRuntime` | Uses `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent()` or `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()` based on `--provider` flag |\n602: | `StatusRuntime` | Uses `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status()` or `AgentCubeProvider.get_agent_runtime()` based on provider |\n603: | `InvokeRuntime` | Uses provider info to construct correct invocation URLs |\n604: | CLI `publish` command | Passes `--provider`, `--node-port`, `--replicas`, `--namespace` options to providers |\n605: \n606: ---\n607: \n608: ## Implementation Notes\n609: \n610: 1. **Kubernetes Client:** Use the official `kubernetes` Python client library\n611: 2. **CRD API Group:** AgentRuntime CR uses `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n612: 3. **Resource Naming:** Both providers share `_sanitize_name()` logic for consistency\n613: 4. **Namespace Handling:** Both providers use `_ensure_namespace()` pattern\n614: 5. **Timeout Defaults:** Default deployment wait timeout is 120 seconds\n615: 6. **NodePort Range:** Valid range is 30000-32767 per Kubernetes specification\n616: 7. **Error Propagation:** Kubernetes API exceptions should be caught and wrapped with context\n617: 8. **Verbose Logging:** Both providers support verbose mode for debugging API calls\n618: 9. **Session Defaults:** AgentRuntime uses `sessionTimeout: \"15m\"` and `maxSessionDuration: \"8h\"`\n619: 10. **Image Pull Secrets:** AgentRuntime always includes `[{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]`\n\n(End of file - total 619 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification: K8s/AgentCube Provider (AR-026)\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-026  \n**Module:** cmd/cli  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Target:** `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`, `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n\nThis delta specification defines the behavior and acceptance criteria for the Kubernetes provider classes that handle agent deployment to both standard Kubernetes (Deployment/Service) and AgentCube custom resources (AgentRuntime CR).\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — Initialization and Configuration\n\nThe system SHALL provide `KubernetesProvider` to interact with Kubernetes clusters for deploying agents using standard Kubernetes resources (Deployment + NodePort Service).\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-026/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775901540545,"end":1775901540573}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775901540579,"sessionID":"ses_28405544effe3GThej4vtHVoCj","part":{"id":"prt_d7bfafc37001bSr3q6t3S7GlQx","messageID":"msg_d7bfad680001d5XtsBK1LBuESF","sessionID":"ses_28405544effe3GThej4vtHVoCj","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-026/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-026/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider\n2: \n3: > **AR ID:** AR-026\n4: > **Module:** `cmd/cli`\n5: > **Language:** Python\n6: > **Size:** M\n7: > **Stage:** ST-3 (Design Completed) → ST-4 (Implementation)\n8: \n9: ---\n10: \n11: ## Overview\n12: \n13: The `KubernetesProvider` and `AgentCubeProvider` classes enable deployment of AI agents to Kubernetes environments using either standard Kubernetes resources (Deployment + NodePort Service) or the AgentCube-specific `AgentRuntime` Custom Resource.\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## ST-4.1 — KubernetesProvider Core Structure\n18: \n19: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n20: |---|------|--------------|------|\n21: | 4.1.1 | Create `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` with `KubernetesProvider` class | File exists with class definition | 0.5h |\n22: | 4.1.2 | Implement `__init__()` with namespace, verbose, kubeconfig parameters | All parameters stored correctly | 0.5h |\n23: | 4.1.3 | Add logger initialization with DEBUG level when verbose=True | Logger configured with DEBUG | 0.25h |\n24: | 4.1.4 | Add `_k8s_client` lazy initialization placeholder | Private attribute initialized to None | 0.25h |\n25: \n26: **Deliverable:** Core provider structure defined.\n27: \n28: ---\n29: \n30: ## ST-4.2 — Kubernetes Client Lazy Initialization\n31: \n32: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n33: |---|------|--------------|------|\n34: | 4.2.1 | Implement `_get_k8s_client()` with kubernetes import check | RuntimeError if kubernetes not installed | 0.5h |\n35: | 4.2.2 | Implement kubeconfig loading: explicit path → default → in-cluster | Loads from provided path first | 0.5hh |\n36: | 4.2.3 | Implement fallback to in-cluster config when kubeconfig fails | In-cluster config loaded as fallback | 0.5h |\n37: | 4.2.4 | Initialize AppsV1Api, CoreV1Api, CustomObjectsApi clients | All three APIs available in dict | 0.5h |\n38: | 4.2.5 | Cache client in `_k8s_client` for reuse | Same client returned on subsequent calls | 0.25h |\n39: | 4.2.6 | Add RuntimeError with helpful message if all config methods fail | Clear error message provided | 0.25h |\n40: \n41: **Deliverable:** Lazy client initialization with multiple config sources.\n42: \n43: ---\n44: \n45: ## ST-4.3 — Namespace Management\n46: \n47: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n48: |---|------|--------------|------|\n49: | 4.3.1 | Implement `_ensure_namespace()` to check namespace exists | Read namespace API call | 0.5h |\n50: | 4.3.2 | Create namespace if not exists (404 handling) | V1Namespace created on 404 | 0.5h |\n51: | 4.3.3 | Handle namespace creation failures gracefully | Appropriate error on failure | 0.5h |\n52: | 4.3.4 | Add debug logging for namespace operations | Logs \"exists\" vs \"created\" | 0.25h |\n53: \n54: **Deliverable:** Automatic namespace management.\n55: \n56: ---\n57: \n58: ## ST-4.4 — KubernetesProvider Deployment Operations\n59: \n60: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n61: |---|------|--------------|------|\n62: | 4.4.1 | Implement `deploy_agent()` with required parameters | Accepts agent_name, image_url, port | 0.5h |\n63: | 4.4.2 | Add NodePort validation (30000-32767 range) | ValueError if outside range | 0.25h |\n64: | 4.4.3 | Call `_ensure_namespace()` before deployment | Namespace ensured | 0.25h |\n65: | 4.4.4 | Call `_create_deployment()` with parameters | Deployment created | 0.5h |\n66: | 4.4.5 | Call `_create_service()` with parameters | Service created | 0.5h |\n67: | 4.4.6 | Return deployment result dict with all required fields | Contains deployment_name, service_name, namespace, replicas, container_port, node_port, service_url, status | 0.5h |\n68: | 4.4.7 | Add logging for deployment lifecycle | Info logs at start and success | 0.25h |\n69: \n70: **Deliverable:** Full agent deployment flow.\n71: \n72: ---\n73: \n74: ## ST-4.5 — Deployment Resource Creation\n75: \n76: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n77: |---|------|--------------|------|\n78: | 4.5.1 | Implement `_create_deployment()` building V1Container spec | Container with name, image, ports | 0.5h |\n79: | 4.5.2 | Add entrypoint parsing (split into command and args) | Command and args set correctly | 0.5h |\n80: | 4.5.3 | Add environment variables as V1EnvVar list | Env vars in container spec | 0.5h |\n81: | 4.5.4 | Build V1PodTemplateSpec with labels | Template with app label | 0.25h |\n82: | 4.5.5 | Build V1Deployment with apps/v1 apiVersion | Proper Deployment structure | 0.5h |\n83: | 4.5.6 | Implement update-or-create pattern (try replace, then create) | Updates existing, creates new | 0.5h |\n84: | 4.5.7 | Handle ApiException 404 for new deployments | Creates on 404, raises on other errors | 0.5h |\n85: | 4.5.8 | Add debug logging for deployment operations | Logs \"Updated\" vs \"Created\" | 0.25h |\n86: \n87: **Deliverable:** Deployment resource CRUD operations.\n88: \n89: ---\n90: \n91: ## ST-4.6 — Service Resource Creation\n92: \n93: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n94: |---|------|--------------|------|\n95: | 4.6.1 | Implement `_create_service()` building V1ServiceSpec with NodePort type | Type set to NodePort | 0.5h |\n96: | 4.6.2 | Configure service ports with port, target_port, node_port | All port mappings correct | 0.5h |\n97: | 4.6.3 | Set selector matching deployment labels | Selector has app label | 0.25h |\n98: | 4.6.4 | Build V1Service with v1 apiVersion | Proper Service structure | 0.25h |\n99: | 4.6.5 | Implement update-or-create pattern for service | Updates existing, creates new | 0.5h |\n100: | 4.6.6 | Retrieve auto-assigned NodePort when not specified | Returns assigned port from created service | 0.5h |\n101: | 4.6.7 | Handle ApiException 404 for new services | Creates on 404, raises on other errors | 0.5h |\n102: | 4.6.8 | Return service result with name and node_port | Dict with correct fields | 0.25h |\n103: \n104: **Deliverable:** NodePort Service resource CRUD operations.\n105: \n106: ---\n107: \n108: ## ST-4.7 — Deployment Status & Waiting\n109: \n110: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n111: |---|------|--------------|------|\n112: | 4.7.1 | Implement `wait_for_deployment_ready()` with timeout parameter | Accepts timeout in seconds | 0.5h |\n113: | 4.7.2 | Poll deployment status every 5 seconds | time.sleep(5) between checks | 0.25h |\n114: | 4.7.3 | Check ready_replicas == replicas == updated_replicas | All conditions met for ready | 0.5h |\n115: | 4.7.4 | Add debug logging showing ready/total count | \"X/Y ready\" logged | 0.25h |\n116: | 4.7.5 | Raise TimeoutError if not ready within timeout | Exception raised on timeout | 0.5h |\n117: | 4.7.6 | Implement `get_agent_status()` returning deployment and service status | Dict with both resources | 0.5h |\n118: | 4.7.7 | Handle 404 errors gracefully in status check | Returns None for missing resources | 0.5h |\n119: | 4.7.8 | Include replica counts and node port in status | Accurate status information | 0.25h |\n120: \n121: **Deliverable:** Deployment readiness monitoring and status retrieval.\n122: \n123: ---\n124: \n125: ## ST-4.8 — KubernetesProvider Cleanup\n126: \n127: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n128: |---|------|--------------|------|\n129: | 4.8.1 | Implement `delete_agent()` to remove deployment | delete_namespaced_deployment called | 0.5h |\n130: | 4.8.2 | Implement service deletion in `delete_agent()` | delete_namespaced_service called | 0.5h |\n131: | 4.8.3 | Handle 404 errors gracefully during deletion | Logs warning, doesn't raise | 0.5h |\n132: | 4.8.4 | Return deletion status dict | Contains status, names, namespace | 0.25h |\n133: | 4.8.5 | Add debug logging for deletion operations | Logs \"Deleted\" messages | 0.25h |\n134: \n135: **Deliverable:** Resource cleanup operations.\n136: \n137: ---\n138: \n139: ## ST-4.9 — AgentCubeProvider Core Structure\n140: \n141: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n142: |---|------|--------------|------|\n143: | 4.9.1 | Create `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` with `AgentCubeProvider` class | File exists with class definition | 0.5h |\n144: | 4.9.2 | Define CRD constants: CRD_GROUP, CRD_VERSION, CRD_PLURAL | Constants match design spec | 0.25h |\n145: | 4.9.3 | Implement `__init__()` with namespace, verbose, kubeconfig | Parameters stored correctly | 0.5h |\n146: | 4.9.4 | Share `_k8s_client` lazy initialization pattern | Same pattern as KubernetesProvider | 0.25h |\n147: \n148: **Deliverable:** AgentCube provider structure.\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ## ST-4.10 — AgentCubeProvider Deployment\n153: \n154: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n155: |---|------|--------------|------|\n156: | 4.10.1 | Implement `deploy_agent_runtime()` with all parameters | Accepts all design spec parameters | 0.5h |\n157: | 4.10.2 | Validate workload_manager_url and router_url are provided | ValueError if either missing | 0.5h |\n158: | 4.10.3 | Call `_ensure_namespace()` before deployment | Namespace ensured | 0.25h |\n159: | 4.10.4 | Call `_build_agent_runtime_spec()` to create CR spec | Spec dict built | 0.5h |\n160: | 4.10.5 | Call `_apply_agent_runtime_cr()` to create/update CR | CR applied | 0.5h |\n161: | 4.10.6 | Return result with agent_id, agent_endpoint, status, URLs | Dict contains all fields | 0.5h |\n162: | 4.10.7 | Add logging for deployment lifecycle | Info logs at start and success | 0.25h |\n163: \n164: **Deliverable:** AgentRuntime CR deployment flow.\n165: \n166: ---\n167: \n168: ## ST-4.11 — AgentRuntime CR Specification Building\n169: \n170: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n171: |---|------|--------------|------|\n172: | 4.11.1 | Implement `_build_agent_runtime_spec()` | Returns spec dict | 0.5h |\n173: | 4.11.2 | Build environment variables including WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL and ROUTER_URL | Required env vars present | 0.5h |\n174: | 4.11.3 | Build container spec with image, ports, env | Proper container structure | 0.5h |\n175: | 4.11.4 | Add entrypoint parsing (command and args) | Entrypoint split correctly | 0.5h |\n176: | 4.11.5 | Add readinessProbe when readiness_probe_path provided | Probe configured with path and port | 0.5h |\n177: | 4.11.6 | Add imagePullSecrets (default to default-secret) | Secrets in pod spec | 0.5h |\n178: | 4.11.7 | Build full AgentRuntime spec with sessionTimeout, maxSessionDuration, podTemplate | Complete spec structure | 0.5h |\n179: \n180: **Deliverable:** AgentRuntime CR specification builder.\n181: \n182: ---\n183: \n184: ## ST-4.12 — AgentRuntime CR Application\n185: \n186: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n187: |---|------|--------------|------|\n188: | 4.12.1 | Implement `_apply_agent_runtime_cr()` with name and spec | Accepts name and spec dict | 0.5h |\n189: | 4.12.2 | Build CR body with apiVersion, kind, metadata, spec | Proper CR structure | 0.5h |\n190: | 4.12.3 | Use CustomObjectsApi for CR operations | custom_api used | 0.5h |\n191: | 4.12.4 | Implement update-or-create pattern | Replaces existing, creates new | 0.5h |\n192: | 4.12.5 | Handle ApiException 404 for new CRs | Creates on 404, raises on other errors | 0.5h |\n193: | 4.12.6 | Add debug logging for CR operations | Logs \"Updated\" vs \"Created\" | 0.25h |\n194: | 4.12.7 | Return CR info dict with name and namespace | Correct return structure | 0.25h |\n195: \n196: **Deliverable:** AgentRuntime CR apply operations.\n197: \n198: ---\n199: \n200: ## ST-4.13 — AgentCubeProvider Status & Cleanup\n201: \n202: | # | T