{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775901837314,"sessionID":"ses_28405544effe3GThej4vtHVoCj","part":{"id":"prt_d7bfc55f2001OYRuhGLropgp9t","messageID":"msg_d7bfbfaae0017S8pUnpL1btqD5","sessionID":"ses_28405544effe3GThej4vtHVoCj","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:15","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Specification: SDK CodeInterpreterClient (AR-027)\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-027  \n**Module:** sdk-python  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Target:** `python-sdk/agentcube/sdk/code_interpreter.py`\n\nThis delta specification defines the behavior and acceptance criteria for the CodeInterpreterClient SDK that provides programmatic access to the Code Interpreter service for secure sandboxed code execution.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterClient — Initialization and Configuration\n\nThe system SHALL provide `CodeInterpreterClient` to interact with the Code Interpreter service.\n\n#### Scenario: Initialize with default configuration\n- **GIVEN** no parameters provided\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient()` is instantiated\n- **THEN** it SHALL default to environment-based configuration\n\n#### Scenario: Initialize with explicit configuration\n- **GIVEN** `base_url`, `api_key`, and optional `timeout` parameters\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(...)` is instantiated\n- **THEN** it SHALL store these values for API calls\n\n#### Scenario: Initialize with custom HTTP client\n- **GIVEN** a custom `http_client` implementing the HTTP interface\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(http_client=...)` is instantiated\n- **THEN** it SHALL use the provided client instead of creating one\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterClient — Session Management\n\nThe system SHALL manage Code Interpreter sessions with automatic lifecycle handling.\n\n#### Scenario: Create new session\n- **GIVEN** valid configuration\n- **WHEN** `create_session()` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return a `Session` object with session_id\n\n#### Scenario: Auto-create session on first execution\n- **GIVEN** no active session exists\n- **WHEN** `execute_code()` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL automatically create a session before execution\n\n#### Scenario: Close session explicitly\n- **GIVEN** an active session\n- **WHEN** `close_session(session_id)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL terminate the session and cleanup resources\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager support\n- **GIVEN** a session created via context manager\n- **WHEN** exiting the context\n- **THEN** it SHALL automatically close the session\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterClient — Code Execution\n\nThe system SHALL execute code in sandboxed environments and return structured results.\n\n#### Scenario: Execute Python code\n- **GIVEN** Python source code as string\n- **WHEN** `execute_code(code, language=\"python\")` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute the code and return `ExecutionResult`\n\n#### Scenario: Execute JavaScript code\n- **GIVEN** JavaScript source code\n- **WHEN** `execute_code(code, language=\"javascript\")` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute in Node.js environment and return results\n\n#### Scenario: Execute Bash commands\n- **GIVEN** shell commands as string\n- **WHEN** `execute_code(code, language=\"bash\")` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute in bash shell and return output\n\n#### Scenario: Execution with timeout\n- **GIVEN** `timeout=30` parameter\n- **WHEN** `execute_code(...)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL enforce the timeout and raise `TimeoutError` if exceeded\n\n#### Scenario: Execution with input data\n- **GIVEN** `input_data` parameter with initial variables/files\n- **WHEN** `execute_code(...)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL make data available to the execution environment\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterClient — Result Handling\n\nThe system SHALL return execution results in a structured format.\n\n#### Scenario: Successful execution result\n- **GIVEN** code executes successfully\n- **WHEN** execution completes\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `ExecutionResult` with stdout, stderr, exit_code=0\n\n#### Scenario: Failed execution result\n- **GIVEN** code raises an exception or exits non-zero\n- **WHEN** execution completes\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `ExecutionResult` with exit_code != 0 and error details\n\n#### Scenario: Result with artifacts\n- **GIVEN** code generates files/images\n- **WHEN** execution completes\n- **THEN** it SHALL return artifact URLs/paths in `ExecutionResult.artifacts`\n\n#### Scenario: Result with execution time\n- **GIVEN** any code execution\n- **WHEN** result is returned\n- **THEN** it SHALL include execution duration in milliseconds\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterClient — File Operations\n\nThe system SHALL support file upload and download for code execution.\n\n#### Scenario: Upload file for execution\n- **GIVEN** a local file path or file-like object\n- **WHEN** `upload_file(session_id, file_path)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL upload the file and return file reference\n\n#### Scenario: Download result file\n- **GIVEN** an artifact path from execution result\n- **WHEN** `download_file(session_id, file_path)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return file content or save to specified path\n\n#### Scenario: List session files\n- **GIVEN** an active session\n- **WHEN** `list_files(session_id)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return list of files in the session workspace\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterClient — Error Handling\n\nThe system SHALL handle errors gracefully with meaningful exceptions.\n\n#### Scenario: Authentication error\n- **GIVEN** invalid or missing API key\n- **WHEN** any API call is made\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `AuthenticationError` with clear message\n\n#### Scenario: Session not found\n- **GIVEN** invalid or expired session_id\n- **WHEN** session operation is attempted\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `SessionNotFoundError`\n\n#### Scenario: Execution timeout\n- **GIVEN** code that exceeds timeout\n- **WHEN** `execute_code()` times out\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ExecutionTimeoutError`\n\n#### Scenario: Rate limit exceeded\n- **GIVEN** too many requests\n- **WHEN** API returns 429\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `RateLimitError` with retry-after info\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterClient — Async API\n\nThe system SHALL provide async versions of all operations.\n\n#### Scenario: Async session creation\n- **GIVEN** async client usage\n- **WHEN** `await client.create_session()` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `AsyncSession` object\n\n#### Scenario: Async code execution\n- **GIVEN** async client usage\n- **WHEN** `await client.execute_code()` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute asynchronously and return result\n\n#### Scenario: Async file operations\n- **GIVEN** async client usage\n- **WHEN** `await client.upload_file()` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL perform upload asynchronously\n\n---\n\n## Data Model Reference\n\n### CodeInterpreterClient Class\n\n```python\nclass CodeInterpreterClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        base_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        api_key: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: float = 30.0,\n        http_client: Optional[HttpClient] = None,\n    ) -> None: ...\n    def create_session(self) -> Session: ...\n    def close_session(self, session_id: str) -> None: ...\n    def execute_code(\n        self,\n        code: str,\n        language: str = \"python\",\n        timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n        input_data: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n    ) -> ExecutionResult: ...\n    def upload_file(self, session_id: str, file_path: Union[str, Path, IO]) -> FileReference: ...\n    def download_file(self, session_id: str, file_path: str) -> bytes: ...\n    def list_files(self, session_id: str) -> List[FileInfo]: ...\n```\n\n### ExecutionResult Class\n\n```python\nclass ExecutionResult:\n    stdout: str\n    stderr: str\n    exit_code: int\n    execution_time_ms: int\n    artifacts: List[Artifact]\n    metadata: Dict[str, Any]\n```\n\n### Session Class\n\n```python\nclass Session:\n    session_id: str\n    created_at: datetime\n    expires_at: Optional[datetime]\n    language: Optional[str]\n    def close(self) -> None: ...\n    def __enter__(self) -> Session: ...\n    def __exit__(self, *args) -> None: ...\n```\n\n---\n\n## File Index\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `python-sdk/agentcube/sdk/code_interpreter.py` | `CodeInterpreterClient` implementation |\n| `python-sdk/agentcube/sdk/models.py` | Data models (ExecutionResult, Session, etc.) |\n| `python-sdk/agentcube/sdk/exceptions.py` | Custom exceptions |\n| `python-sdk/agentcube/sdk/__init__.py` | SDK package exports |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|\n| `httpx>=0.25.0` | HTTP client for API calls |\n| `pydantic>=2.0.0` | Data validation and models |\n| `tenacity>=8.0.0` | Retry logic |\n\n---\n\n## Integration Points\n\n| Component | Integration |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| Code Interpreter Service | REST API calls to `/v1/sessions`, `/v1/execute` |\n| Authentication | API key in Authorization header |\n| Session Store | Server-side session management |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n1. **HTTP Client:** Use `httpx` for both sync and async operations\n2. **Retry Logic:** Use `tenacity` for automatic retries on transient errors\n3. **Session Management:** Support both explicit and automatic session handling\n4. **Language Support:** Start with Python, extend to JavaScript and Bash\n5. **Error Handling:** Custom exception hierarchy for different error types\n6. **Timeouts:** Configurable per-request and global timeouts\n7. **Type Hints:** Full type annotation support\n8. **Context Managers:** Support `with` statement for session lifecycle\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-025/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775901837279,"end":1775901837312}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775901837316,"sessionID":"ses_28405544effe3GThej4vtHVoCj","part":{"id":"prt_d7bfd213d001y8AxkEeSXHHO3K","messageID":"msg_d7bfbfaae0017S8pUnpL1btqD5","sessionID":"ses_28405544effe3GThej4vtHVoCj","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:16","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-027/plan.md","content":"# AR-027: SDK CodeInterpreterClient — Implementation Plan\n\n## Phase 1: Foundation\n- [ ] Create CodeInterpreterClient class structure\n- [ ] Define data model schemas using Pydantic\n- [ ] Implement HTTP client abstraction with httpx\n- [ ] Set up configuration management\n- [ ] Define custom exception hierarchy\n\n## Phase 2: Session Management\n- [ ] Implement session creation\n- [ ] Implement session closure\n- [ ] Add context manager support\n- [ ] Implement auto-session creation\n- [ ] Add session lifecycle hooks\n\n## Phase 3: Code Execution\n- [ ] Implement basic code execution\n- [ ] Add language parameter support\n- [ ] Implement timeout handling\n- [ ] Add input data injection\n- [ ] Handle execution results\n\n## Phase 4: File Operations\n- [ ] Implement file upload\n- [ ] Implement file download\n- [ ] Add file listing\n- [ ] Handle binary and text files\n- [ ] Add file validation\n\n## Phase 5: Async API\n- [ ] Create AsyncCodeInterpreterClient\n- [ ] Implement async session management\n- [ ] Implement async code execution\n- [ ] Implement async file operations\n- [ ] Add async context managers\n\n## Phase 6: Error Handling & Testing\n- [ ] Implement retry logic with tenacity\n- [ ] Add comprehensive error handling\n- [ ] Write unit tests with mocks\n- [ ] Write integration tests\n- [ ] Add type checking with mypy\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-025/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-027/plan.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-027/plan.md","time":{"start":1775901837283,"end":1775901837315}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775901837317,"sessionID":"ses_28405544effe3GThej4vtHVoCj","part":{"id":"prt_d7bfd41fd001Yg4m60W7TPqAPR","messageID":"msg_d7bfbfaae0017S8pUnpL1btqD5","sessionID":"ses_28405544effe3GThej4vtHVoCj","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:17","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-027/design.md","content":"# AR-027: SDK CodeInterpreterClient — Design Document\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Diagram\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────┐\n│  User Application   │\n│  (Agent/Service)    │\n└──────────┬──────────┘\n           │\n           ▼\n┌─────────────────────┐\n│ CodeInterpreter     │\n│ Client              │\n│(Sync & Async APIs)  │\n└──────────┬──────────┘\n           │\n     ┌─────┴─────┐\n     ▼           ▼\n┌─────────┐ ┌─────────┐\n│ Session │ │ HTTP    │\n│ Manager │ │ Client  │\n└────┬────┘ └────┬────┘\n     │           │\n     ▼           ▼\n┌─────────┐ ┌─────────┐\n│ Session │ │ Code    │\n│ State   │ │ Interpreter\n└─────────┘ │ Service │\n            └─────────┘\n```\n\n## Key Design Decisions\n\n### Client Architecture\n- Single client class supporting both sync and async operations\n- Async client available as `AsyncCodeInterpreterClient`\n- Shared configuration and models between sync/async\n- Lazy initialization of HTTP client\n\n### Session Management\n- Server-side session state management\n- Client-side session reference tracking\n- Automatic session cleanup on context exit\n- Optional auto-create on first execution\n\n### HTTP Client Design\n- Use `httpx` for both sync and async HTTP operations\n- Configurable timeouts at client and request level\n- Automatic retries for transient failures\n- Connection pooling for efficiency\n\n### Data Models\n- Pydantic v2 models for validation\n- Immutable result objects\n- Rich metadata for debugging\n- Type-safe throughout\n\n### Error Handling\n- Custom exception hierarchy\n- Automatic retry with exponential backoff\n- Clear error messages with context\n- Graceful degradation\n\n## Data Flow\n\n1. User application calls `client.execute_code()`\n2. Client ensures session exists (create if needed)\n3. HTTP client sends POST to `/v1/execute`\n4. Service executes code in sandbox\n5. Result returned as JSON\n6. Client parses into `ExecutionResult` model\n7. User receives structured result object\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n- API key stored securely, never logged\n- Session isolation between users\n- File access restricted to session workspace\n- Execution timeouts prevent resource exhaustion\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-025/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-027/design.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-027/design.md","time":{"start":1775901837286,"end":1775901837316}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775901837319,"sessionID":"ses_28405544effe3GThej4vtHVoCj","part":{"id":"prt_d7bfd7234001OxKuyChpfpuWbr","messageID":"msg_d7bfbfaae0017S8pUnpL1btqD5","sessionID":"ses_28405544effe3GThej4vtHVoCj","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:18","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-027/tests.md","content":"# AR-027: SDK CodeInterpreterClient — Test Specification\n\n## Unit Tests\n\n### Client Initialization Tests\n- `test_init_with_defaults`: Environment variables used\n- `test_init_with_explicit_config`: Config stored correctly\n- `test_init_with_custom_http_client`: Custom client used\n- `test_init_missing_api_key`: Raises ConfigurationError\n- `test_init_missing_base_url`: Raises ConfigurationError\n\n### Session Management Tests\n- `test_create_session_returns_session`: Session object returned\n- `test_create_session_makes_api_call`: POST /v1/sessions called\n- `test_close_session_makes_api_call`: DELETE /v1/sessions called\n- `test_session_context_manager`: Auto-closes on exit\n- `test_auto_create_session`: Session created on first execute\n- `test_session_not_found_raises`: SessionNotFoundError raised\n\n### Code Execution Tests\n- `test_execute_python_success`: Result with exit_code=0\n- `test_execute_javascript_success`: JS code executed\n- `test_execute_bash_success`: Shell command executed\n- `test_execute_with_timeout`: Timeout respected\n- `test_execute_timeout_exceeded`: ExecutionTimeoutError raised\n- `test_execute_with_input_data`: Data available in execution\n- `test_execute_invalid_language`: ValueError raised\n\n### Result Handling Tests\n- `test_result_has_stdout`: stdout populated\n- `test_result_has_stderr`: stderr populated\n- `test_result_has_exit_code`: exit_code present\n- `test_result_has_execution_time`: duration in ms\n- `test_result_with_artifacts`: artifacts list populated\n- `test_result_failed_execution`: exit_code != 0\n\n### File Operation Tests\n- `test_upload_file_success`: FileReference returned\n- `test_upload_file_from_path`: File uploaded from disk\n- `test_upload_file_from_bytes`: File uploaded from memory\n- `test_download_file_success`: Content returned\n- `test_download_file_save_to_path`: File written to disk\n- `test_list_files_returns_file_info`: FileInfo list returned\n\n### Error Handling Tests\n- `test_authentication_error`: AuthenticationError raised\n- `test_rate_limit_error`: RateLimitError with retry_after\n- `test_server_error`: ServerError raised\n- `test_connection_error`: ConnectionError raised\n- `test_validation_error`: ValidationError raised\n- `test_error_includes_response`: Error has response details\n\n### Retry Logic Tests\n- `test_retries_on_500`: Retries on server error\n- `test_retries_on_timeout`: Retries on timeout\n- `test_no_retry_on_400`: No retry on client error\n- `test_max_retries_exceeded`: MaxRetryError raised\n\n## Async Tests\n\n### Async Client Tests\n- `test_async_init`: AsyncClient initializes\n- `test_async_create_session`: Session created asynchronously\n- `test_async_execute_code`: Code executed asynchronously\n- `test_async_upload_file`: File uploaded asynchronously\n- `test_async_context_manager`: Async context manager works\n\n## Integration Tests\n\n### Happy Path\n- `test_full_execution_lifecycle`: Create → Execute → Close\n- `test_session_reuse`: Multiple executions in one session\n- `test_file_upload_execute`: Upload then execute with file\n- `test_download_artifact`: Execute then download result\n\n### Error Scenarios\n- `test_invalid_api_key`: Authentication fails\n- `test_expired_session`: Session timeout handled\n- `test_large_file_upload`: Size limits handled\n- `test_concurrent_executions`: Parallel execution handled\n\n## Test Data\n- Sample Python/JavaScript/Bash code fixtures\n- Mock HTTP responses\n- Test file binaries\n- Session state fixtures\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-025/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-027/tests.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-027/tests.md","time":{"start":1775901837289,"end":1775901837318}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775901837321,"sessionID":"ses_28405544effe3GThej4vtHVoCj","part":{"id":"prt_d7bfdb7b8001FL2cn5Ud0otR3Q","messageID":"msg_d7bfbfaae0017S8pUnpL1btqD5","sessionID":"ses_28405544effe3GThej4vtHVoCj","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:19","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-027/tasks.md","content":"# AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n\n> **AR ID:** AR-027\n> **Module:** `sdk-python`\n> **Language:** Python\n> **Size:** M\n> **Stage:** ST-1 (Initialized)\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nThe `CodeInterpreterClient` provides a Python SDK for interacting with the Code Interpreter service, enabling secure sandboxed code execution for AI agents and applications.\n\n---\n\n## ST-1.1 — Project Structure and Dependencies\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 1.1.1 | Create `python-sdk/agentcube/sdk/` directory structure | Directory exists | 0.25h |\n| 1.1.2 | Update `python-sdk/pyproject.toml` with httpx dependency | httpx>=0.25.0 in deps | 0.25h |\n| 1.1.3 | Update `python-sdk/pyproject.toml` with tenacity dependency | tenacity>=8.0.0 in deps | 0.25h |\n| 1.1.4 | Update `python-sdk/pyproject.toml` with pydantic dependency | pydantic>=2.0.0 in deps | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** SDK dependencies configured.\n\n---\n\n## ST-1.2 — Exception Hierarchy\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 1.2.1 | Create `python-sdk/agentcube/sdk/exceptions.py` | File exists | 0.25h |\n| 1.2.2 | Implement `CodeInterpreterError` base exception | Class defined | 0.25h |\n| 1.2.3 | Implement `AuthenticationError` exception | Class defined | 0.25h |\n| 1.2.4 | Implement `SessionNotFoundError` exception | Class defined | 0.25h |\n| 1.2.5 | Implement `ExecutionTimeoutError` exception | Class defined | 0.25h |\n| 1.2.6 | Implement `RateLimitError` exception with retry_after | Class defined | 0.25h |\n| 1.2.7 | Implement `ValidationError` exception | Class defined | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Complete exception hierarchy.\n\n---\n\n## ST-1.3 — Data Models\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 1.3.1 | Create `python-sdk/agentcube/sdk/models.py` | File exists | 0.25h |\n| 1.3.2 | Implement `ExecutionResult` Pydantic model | Model validates | 0.5h |\n| 1.3.3 | Implement `Session` Pydantic model | Model validates | 0.5h |\n| 1.3.4 | Implement `FileReference` Pydantic model | Model validates | 0.25h |\n| 1.3.5 | Implement `FileInfo` Pydantic model | Model validates | 0.25h |\n| 1.3.6 | Implement `Artifact` Pydantic model | Model validates | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** All data models defined.\n\n---\n\n## ST-1.4 — HTTP Client Abstraction\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 1.4.1 | Create `python-sdk/agentcube/sdk/http_client.py` | File exists | 0.25h |\n| 1.4.2 | Implement `HttpClient` protocol/interface | Protocol defined | 0.5h |\n| 1.4.3 | Implement `HttpxClient` wrapper class | Wraps httpx.Client | 0.5h |\n| 1.4.4 | Add retry configuration with tenacity | Retries on failures | 0.5h |\n| 1.4.5 | Implement `AsyncHttpxClient` for async operations | Wraps httpx.AsyncClient | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** HTTP client abstraction layer.\n\n---\n\n## ST-1.5 — CodeInterpreterClient Core Structure\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 1.5.1 | Create `python-sdk/agentcube/sdk/code_interpreter.py` | File exists | 0.25h |\n| 1.5.2 | Implement `CodeInterpreterClient` class definition | Class defined | 0.25h |\n| 1.5.3 | Implement `__init__()` with base_url, api_key, timeout | Parameters stored | 0.5h |\n| 1.5.4 | Add lazy initialization of HTTP client | Client created on first use | 0.25h |\n| 1.5.5 | Add logger initialization | Logger configured | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Core client structure defined.\n\n---\n\n## ST-