{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775901837688,"sessionID":"ses_28405544effe3GThej4vtHVoCj","part":{"id":"prt_d7bfc29af001BpIff3PxOveIcW","messageID":"msg_d7bfbfaae0017S8pUnpL1btqD5","sessionID":"ses_28405544effe3GThej4vtHVoCj","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:14","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-027/spec.yaml","content":"id: AR-027\ntitle: SDK CodeInterpreterClient\nmodule: sdk-python\nlanguage: Python\nsize: M\nstatus: open\n\n# AR-027: SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n# Module: sdk-python\n# Language: Python\n# Size: M\n\n# OpenSpec Metadata\nopenspec:\n  version: \"1.0\"\n  project: agentcube\n\n# Architecture Requirement\nrequirement:\n  type: sdk-client\n  description: |\n    Implement a CodeInterpreterClient class within the sdk-python module to provide\n    a Python SDK client for the Code Interpreter service. This client will enable\n    programmatic code execution, session management, and result retrieval for\n    AI agents and applications that need secure sandboxed code execution capabilities.\n\n# Scope\nscope:\n  in:\n    - CodeInterpreterClient class implementation\n    - Session lifecycle management (create, manage, close)\n    - Code execution with multiple language support\n    - Result retrieval and formatting\n    - File upload/download capabilities\n    - Error handling and retry logic\n    - Async/sync API support\n    - Authentication and authorization integration\n  out:\n    - WebSocket real-time streaming (separate AR)\n    - Multi-region load balancing (separate AR)\n    - Client-side caching (separate AR)\n    - CLI interface for SDK (separate AR)\n\n# Acceptance Criteria\nacceptance:\n  - CodeInterpreterClient provides clean API for code execution\n  - Session management handles lifecycle automatically\n  - Multiple programming languages supported (Python, JavaScript, Bash)\n  - Results returned in structured format with stdout, stderr, artifacts\n  - File operations work with binary and text files\n  - Proper error handling with meaningful exceptions\n  - Both sync and async APIs available\n  - Unit testable with mock server\n\n# References\nreferences:\n  - https://docs.python.org/3/library/httpx/\n  - https://pypi.org/project/tenacity/\n  - https://docs.pydantic.dev/\n\n# Estimation\nestimation:\n  size: M\n  story_points: 5\n  days: 3\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-025/spec.yaml":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-027/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-027/spec.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-027/spec.yaml","time":{"start":1775901837271,"end":1775901837684}}}}
